Configuration

•	Configure Git with your name: git config --global user.name "Your Name"
•	Configure Git with your email: git config --global user.email "youremail@example.com"
Creating and Cloning Repositories
•	Initialize a new Git repository: git init
•	Clone a remote repository: git clone remote_repository_url


Basic Git Workflow

•	Check the status of your working directory: git status
•	Stage changes for commit: git add file_name
•	Unstage changes: git reset file_name
•	Commit changes with a message: git commit -m "Your commit message"
•	Push changes to a remote repository: git push
•	Pull changes from a remote repository: git pull

Branching and Merging

•	Create a new branch: git branch branch_name
•	Switch to a branch: git checkout branch_name
•	Create a new branch and switch to it: git checkout -b branch_name
•	Merge a branch into the current branch: git merge branch_name
•	Delete a branch: git branch -d branch_name

Viewing History

•	Show commit history: git log
•	Show a specific commit and its changes: git show commit_hash
Remote Repositories
•	Add a remote repository: git remote add remote_name remote_repository_url
•	Fetch changes from a remote repository: git fetch remote_name
•	Remove a remote repository: git remote remove remote_name

Undoing Changes

•	Discard changes in the working directory: git checkout -- file_name
•	Revert a commit and create a new commit: git revert commit_hash
•	Reset to a previous commit and discard subsequent changes: git reset --hard commit_hash
Tagging
•	Create an annotated tag: git tag -a tag_name -m "Tag message"
•	Push tags to a remote repository: git push origin tag_name
•	Show a list of tags: git tag

Stashing

•	Temporarily save changes without committing: git stash
•	Apply stashed changes: git stash apply
•	List stashed changes: git stash list
This cheat sheet includes many common Git commands and should be a handy reference for basic Git operations. Remember to replace placeholders like file_name, branch_name, and commit_hash with your specific information when using these commands.
